FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE - SOUTH KOREA (01): (NORTH JEOLLA) PORCINE, SEROTYPE O, OIE
*******************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 12 Jan 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information 2016; 29(02) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=19489


Foot-and-mouth disease, Korea (Rep. of)
----------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 12 Jan 2016 from Dr Oh Soon-Min, Director, Chief Veterinary Officer, General Animal Health Division, Ministry of Agriculture, Food and Rural Affairs (MAFRA), Sejong-Si, Korea (Rep. of)

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 11 Jan 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 12 Jan 2016
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 22 May 2015
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot-and-mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Yongji-myeon, Gimje-si, Jeollabuk-Do [North Jeolla]
Date of start of the outbreak: 11 Jan 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved no provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 670 / 30 / 0 / 670 / 0
Affected population: domestic swine
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine / 4.48 / 0 / 0 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: Epidemiological survey is currently being implemented. Infected animals were destroyed.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; screening; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); disinfection/disinfestations; quarantine; stamping out; control of wildlife reservoirs; zoning; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Animal and Plant Quarantine Agency (national laboratory) / Swine / antigen (Ag) detection ELISA / 12 Jan 2016 / Positive
Animal and Plant Quarantine Agency (national laboratory) / Swine / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 12 Jan 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-MBDS
<promed-mbds@promedmail.org>

[Prior to this current outbreak, the last event of FMD serotype O was on 3 Dec 2014, when a total of 185 outbreaks were reported. According to the final report on 21 Jun 2015 (http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/temp/reports/en_fup_0000017970_20150622_144707.pdf), the event was resolved on 22 May 2015. See the event summary and map at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=16695. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3929657,21446.]
